In [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 5 (1577), Motochika launched his invasion of Awa. The current head, Kakuyō, initially sought peace by offering his brother, Yoritomo, as a hostage. However, he soon defected to the [[:en:Miyoshi clan|Miyoshi clan]] at their request.

Motochika responded by capturing {{ill|Tao Castle|ja|田尾城|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tao Castle|qq=|1=Tao Castle|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11576557}}, a key fortification of Hakuchi Castle, within just two days, guided by the hostage Yoritomo. While Kakuyō fled to Sanuki, Yoritake is said to have committed seppuku during the conflict.
